<title>SOUTH AFRICA: RUGBY UNION-BRITISH LIONS BEAT SOUTH AFRICA TO TAKE SERIES.</title>
<headline>RUGBY UNION-BRITISH LIONS BEAT SOUTH AFRICA TO TAKE SERIES.</headline>
<dateline>DURBAN, South Africa 1997-06-28</dateline>
<text>
<p>The British Lions beat South Africa 18-15 (halftime 6-5) in the second test on Saturday.</p>
<p>The Lions won the first test in Capetown 26-18 to take a 2-0 winning lead in the three-test series.</p>
